{% block examples %}
### Basic example

Use the `Switch` component on its own to render a standalone switch without an associated `Label` component:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Basic example', {height: '122px'}) }}

Make sure to provide an `aria-label` for assistive technology, or connect the `Switch` to your own `<label>` element using an `id`.

### With label

Wrap a `Fieldset:Label` and `Switch` with the `Switch:Field` component to automatically associate them:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With label', {height: '122px'}) }}

### With description

Use the `Switch:Field`, `Fieldset:Label`, and `Fieldset:Description` components to add a label and description to a switch:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With description', {height: '150px'}) }}

### With accent color

Use the `color` prop to choose a different accent color for a switch:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With accent color', {height: '122px'}) }}

### With custom value

Use the `value` attribute to specify a custom value to use when submitting a form:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With custom value', {height: '122px'}) }}

### Default checked state

Use the `checked` attribute to set the default state of the switch:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Default checked state', {height: '122px'}) }}

### Multiple switches

Use the `Switch:Group` component to stack multiple switches together in a list:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Multiple switches', {height: '250px'}) }}

You can optionally add `role="group"` and an `aria-label` to the `Switch:Group` if all of the switches are related and you want them announced to assistive technology as a group.

### With fieldset

Use the `Fieldset`, `Fieldset:Legend`, and `Text` components to add a title and description to a group of switches:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With fieldset', {height: '326px'}) }}

### Disabled state

Add the `disabled` prop to a `Switch` or `Switch:Field` component to disable it:

{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Disabled state', {height: '326px'}) }}

You can also add the `disabled` prop to a `Fieldset` to disable the entire fieldset.
